    base:desc "A robust fidelity and validity protocol balances analytical simplicity with realistic dynamics. The twin employs a multi‑resolution modeling hierarchy: lower‑order kinematics models for rapid controller tuning, and higher‑order dynamic models that incorporate detailed motor electrical characteristics, gearbox backlash, and nonlinear friction. Validation is performed by systematic comparison of simulated joint trajectories against measured data collected during a calibration routine. The deviation metric employs the mean absolute deviation over a five‑second test step, with a threshold of <0.05 degrees for position and <0.3 degrees per second for velocity. Exceedances trigger a re‑parameterization loop where parameters are adjusted via a gradient‑based optimizer. Uncertainty quantification is performed through Monte‑Carlo simulation of sensor noise and component tolerances, yielding confidence intervals for predicted states. Error detection is integrated at both data and model levels: outlier filtering removes transient spikes, while residual analysis flags model mismatch when the difference between predicted and measured signals exceeds three sigma. Quality assurance is maintained through automated regression tests that run on every code and model revision, generating a signed “fit report” that documents validation status, test coverage, and any identified regressions."
